Hong Kong Stocks Close 1.31 Percent Higher
HONG KONG , December 24 ( Xinhua ) -- Hong Kong stocks gained 133.45 points , or 1.31 percent , to close at 10,292.20 in the half day trading Thursday ahead of holiday break .
The turnover amounted to 1,514 million HK dollars ( 194.1 million U.S. dollars ) .
The market opened higher with Hang Seng Index rising 88.03 points , or 0.87 percent , to 10 , 246.78 .
The share prices at the sub-sectors of finance , utilities , properties , commerce and industry all registered big gains ranging from 95.50 to 185.83 points .
Local dealers attributed the sharp rise in the half day trading mainly to the Wall Street 's buoyant overnight performance and to Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa 's remarks calling for a harmonious community .
Hong Kong stocks will close on Christmas holidays and resume normal full day trading on December 28 .
